headline: New Research in a New England Journal of Medicine Publication Finds Patients of Value-Based Care Organizations Have More Frequent and Consistent Primary Care Visits
summary: LOUISVILLE, Ky., September 17, 2025--A new study published in The New England Journal of Medicine Catalyst, conducted by the Humana Healthcare Research team and Massachusetts General Hospital Attending Physician Dr. Suhas Gondi, who completed the research while a resident physician at Harvard Medical School's Brigham and Women's Hospital, finds that patients who receive care from senior-focused primary care organizations that practice value-based care are more likely to regularly use primary car
